<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/10149840-sandi">Sandi</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I realize this is an old post, but thought I would add a thought. You can add the Kindle app to your Nook. You can also add the Kindle app to a smart <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I realize this is an old post, but thought I would add a thought. You can add the Kindle app to your Nook. You can also add the Kindle app to a smart phone or other tablet if you have others. The app is free. I do a lot of reading in the doctor's office on my IPhone using the Kindle app. Works great. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
