<div id="review_4151477972" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4151477972" />
    <a title="jessica" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10171516-jessica"><img alt="jessica" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1509983330p2/10171516.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4151477972?book_show_action=true">Aug 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="jessica" class="user" itemprop="url" name="jessica" href="/user/show/10171516-jessica">jessica</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4151477972" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14433658079441093439">this was fine. there were a few things i liked and some things that i didnt.<br/><br/>the case/plot is interesting, the pacing is pretty quick, and there is enough content that kept me interested in continuing the story. <br/><br/>but i didnt quite understand some of the writing choices. the narrative should have excluded the chapters from the murderers POV. they honestly dont add anything of value and ultimately remove any sort of suspense in terms of nicks innocence or guilt. it would have been much more interest</span>
  <span id="freeText14433658079441093439" style="display:none">this was fine. there were a few things i liked and some things that i didnt.<br /><br />the case/plot is interesting, the pacing is pretty quick, and there is enough content that kept me interested in continuing the story. <br /><br />but i didnt quite understand some of the writing choices. the narrative should have excluded the chapters from the murderers POV. they honestly dont add anything of value and ultimately remove any sort of suspense in terms of nicks innocence or guilt. it would have been much more interesting to leave that a mystery, allowing the reader process the evidence as it comes and to think one way or the other until the killers identity is revealed. knowing nick is innocent right from the beginning takes away this basic thrill. <br /><br />i also didnt like that this is marketed as romantic suspense (its even published by a romance publisher!) and yet there is practically zero romance in this. two people deciding to not act on their feelings because the case is more important does not constitute romance for me. <br /><br />overall, not quite the story i was wanting, but it was decent enough for me to see it through to the end. <br /><br /><b>↠ <i>2.5 stars</i></b></span>
  <a data-text-id="14433658079441093439" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


